		<title type="html"><![CDATA[Paper Evolution - Nordic Game Jam 2011 Finalist]]></title>

		
		<content type="html" xml:base="http://love2d.org/forums/viewtopic.php?p=25905#p25905"><![CDATA[
Hi Lovers<br><br>I attended Nordic Game Jam 2011 (part of Global Game Jam) along with Matias Billeschou (graphics) and Simon Leander Mikkelsen (game design). At the jam we met and teamed up with Anders Monrad (sound). The theme was extinction. <br><br>Our game is called Paper Evolution and is puzzle game about erasing lines in a 2D platform environment so our hero is able to to advance through the ages and avoid extinction. We were 1 of 12 finalists chosen out of about 50 games.<br><br><img src="http://lukasz.dk/files/Paper%20Evolution.png" class="postimage" alt="Image"><br><br> <strong>iframe</strong> <br><br><a href="http://lukasz.dk/files/PaperEvolution.love" class="postlink">PaperEvolution.love</a> - Works with latest revision of LÖVE. Crashes after a while in LÖVE 0.7.0<br><br><a href="http://globalgamejam.org/2011/paper-evolution" class="postlink">Global Game Jam site</a> - Mac OS X binary available at the moment.  Please vote/comment <img class="smilies" src="http://love2d.org/forums/images/smilies/ms-smile.png" width="16" height="16" alt=":)" title="Smile"><br><br><a href="https://github.com/lukaszbruun/Paper-Evolution" class="postlink">GitHub</a><br><br>Let us know what you think <img class="smilies" src="http://love2d.org/forums/images/smilies/ms-smile.png" width="16" height="16" alt=":)" title="Smile"><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://love2d.org/forums/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=1802">Lukasz</a> — Mon Jan 31, 2011 12:28 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
